e [Pangeo Showcase](https://discourse.pangeo.io/t/pangeo-showcase-frost-federated-registry-of-scientific-things-feb-12-2025/4861) ([recording here](https://youtu.be/GZvJ0H89G0A)). If you are interested in helping build the thing please [fill","key":"tJLoFEpXLu"}],"key":"q58eHYzy5C"},{"type":"footer","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Date: ","key":"SRwi78koYp"}],"key":"EveadfMpnE"},{"type":"text","value":"January 18, 2025 | ","key":"m4SCZBYrMm"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author: ","key":"PYuMjM64hh"}],"key":"WEbClC662t"},{"type":"text","value":"Tom Nicholas","key":"r5Ylny1qh1"}],"key":"Rg94o7L2E7"}],"urlSource":"/blog/2025/science-needs-a-social-network","key":"Bt157AMTw1"},{"type":"card","url":"/blog/2024/datatree","children":[{"type":"cardTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Xarray x NASA: xarray.DataTree for hierarchical data structures","key":"HqoF5SL17J"}],"key":"UgHtMPqac9"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n\n(Originally posted on the [Xarray blog](https://xarray.dev/blog/datatree).)\n\n\n[`xarray.DataTree`](https://docs.xarray.dev/en/stable/user-guide/data-structures.html#datatree) has been [released](https://github.com/pydata/xarray/discussions/9680) in [v2024.10.0](https://github.com/pydata/xarray/releases/tag/v2024.10.0), and the prototype [`xarray-contrib/datatree` repository](https://github.com/xarray-contrib/datatree) archived, after collaboration between the xarray team and the [NASA ESDIS project](https://www.earthdata.nasa.gov/about/esdis). ü§ù\n\n\nThe DataTree concept allows for organizing heterogeneous collections of scientific data in the same way that a nested directory structure facilitates organizing","key":"oM6lcZbOgl"}],"key":"a7afqjc1s0"},{"type":"footer","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Date: ","key":"TjqGXViZEg"}],"key":"GWufmVli6o"},{"type":"text","value":"December 19, 2024 | ","key":"ddPm2EuvEC"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author: ","key":"thphrgZHRg"}],"key":"khYaOLg8eQ"},{"type":"text","value":"Tom Nicholas","key":"a3xrGBguM2"}],"key":"vY8jamVGHD"}],"urlSource":"/blog/2024/datatree","key":"xUsvlvCUJo"},{"type":"card","url":"/blog/2023/cubed-xarray","children":[{"type":"cardTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cubed: Bounded-memory serverless array processing in xarray","key":"wdMjBcwoCg"}],"key":"G1pDAeqW5O"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n\n_TLDR: Xarray can now wrap a range of parallel computation backends, including [Cubed](https://github.com/tomwhite/cubed), a distributed serverless framework designed to limit memory usage.\n\n\nOne of Xarray's most powerful features is parallel computing on larger-than-memory datasets through its [integration with Dask](https://docs.xarray.dev/en/stable/user-guide/dask.html). \nWe love Dask - it's an incredibly powerful tool, a big part","key":"UuiesXtr87"}],"key":"dJOQRpKPcK"},{"type":"footer","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Date: ","key":"E5SMtfGBvO"}],"key":"irzQE7TPqg"},{"type":"text","value":"June 01, 2023 | ","key":"judPe26zWs"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author: ","key":"Cl9ptma2RL"}],"key":"no91dPmZDs"},{"type":"text","value":"Tom Nicholas","key":"R3yUfQQQRh"}],"key":"kh0MoN3Fcu"}],"urlSource":"/blog/2023/cubed-xarray","key":"Pk4C41tkJK"},{"type":"card","url":"/blog/2023/dask-distributed","children":[{"type":"cardTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Dask.distributed and Pangeo: Better performance for everyone thanks to science / software collaboration","key":"bWQ4ywEd0F"}],"key":"ajrPj6aAki"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n\nBy Tom Nicholas and Ryan Abernathey\n\n(Originally posted on the [Pangeo Medium blog](https://medium.com/pangeo/dask-distributed-and-pangeo-better-performance-for-everyone-thanks-to-science-software-63f85310a36b).)\n\n\n- Pangeo aimed to make big data analysis easy for scientists\n- But awkwardly dask.distributed would fail at large scales‚Ä¶\n- It‚Äôs now fixed, hooray for scientist-developer collaboration!\n\n\nThe [Climate Data Science Lab](https://medium.com/pangeo/announcing-the-climate-data-science-lab-funded-by-the-moore-foundation-4bc4314ac02d) (funded by the Gordon and Betty Moore Foundation) was","key":"D8edFcBBYV"}],"key":"OkHeWCnHm1"},{"type":"footer","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Date: ","key":"TEJy39S6NM"}],"key":"ifeg2zZq3s"},{"type":"text","value":"January 04, 2023 | ","key":"CZII5iAMOW"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author: ","key":"CZXrMLA2kM"}],"key":"SzM298OhDw"},{"type":"text","value":"Tom Nicholas","key":"WBTAyW5NMB"}],"key":"rTANVs9k5Y"}],"urlSource":"/blog/2023/dask-distributed","key":"N9mWtX2dss"},{"type":"card","url":"/blog/2022/pint-xarray","children":[{"type":"cardTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Unit-aware arithmetic in Xarray, via pint","key":"Y2uGjvYJ7f"}],"key":"ThMblGFyAr"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n\n(This post was originally published on the [xarray blog](https://xarray.dev/blog/introducing-pint-xarray).)\n\n_TLDR: Pint-Xarray supports unit-aware operations by wrapping [pint arrays](https://pint.readthedocs.io/en/stable/), so your code can automatically track the physical units that your data represents:_\n\n```python\ndistance = xr.DataArray(10).pint.quantify(\"metres\")\ntime = xr.DataArray(4).pint.quantify(\"seconds\")\n\ndistance / time\n```\n\n```\nOut:\n<xarray.DataArray ()>\n<Quantity(2.5, 'meter / second')>\n```\n\n\nAll quantities in science have units, whether explicitly or implicitly. (And","key":"SjMMqTIZ8l"}],"key":"EXTQ8mNQuJ"},{"type":"footer","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Date: ","key":"MxD4e029xm"}],"key":"IRXhSulx55"},{"type":"text","value":"August 30, 2022 | ","key":"qTh4guol1c"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author: ","key":"ju3og5yKf3"}],"key":"n5RwE9bhOA"},{"type":"text","value":"Tom Nicholas","key":"lGxSQYWoGz"}],"key":"wLIInhKxhe"}],"urlSource":"/blog/2022/pint-xarray","key":"O5IG5SlC8S"},{"type":"card","url":"/blog/2022/easy-IPCC-datatree","children":[{"type":"cardTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Easy IPCC part 1: Multi-Model Datatree","key":"CJzczJih6y"}],"key":"BNpPrJJFSR"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n\n\n*By Tom Nicholas ([@TomNicholas](https://github.com/TomNicholas)) and Julius Busecke ([@jbusecke](https://github.com/jbusecke))*\n\n(Originally posted on the [Pangeo Medium blog](https://medium.com/pangeo/easy-ipcc-part-1-multi-model-datatree-469b87cf9114))\n\nIn this series of blog posts we aim to quickly reproduce a panel from one of the [key figures (fig. 9.3a)](https://github.com/BrodiePearson/IPCC_AR6_Chapter9_Figures/blob/main/Plotting_code_and_data/Fig9_03_SST/Fig9_03_SST.png) of the [IPCC AR6 Report](https://www.ipcc.ch/report/ar6/wg3/) from the raw climate model simulation data, using Pangeo cloud-native tools.","key":"F0eQ0xrhBK"}],"key":"qEwYhdIYgj"},{"type":"footer","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Date: ","key":"Ggn1vm3HKU"}],"key":"JOi35H6fjY"},{"type":"text","value":"August 29, 2022 | ","key":"gz8DrJ1lWO"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author: ","key":"oBCjKO5EgF"}],"key":"sQIPyOkvQW"},{"type":"text","value":"Tom Nicholas","key":"TMlAs6yjRc"}],"key":"yHIlkMJBOA"}],"urlSource":"/blog/2022/easy-IPCC-datatree","key":"JDK7RfBGVV"},{"type":"card","url":"/blog/2020/deep-pseudoscience","children":[{"type":"cardTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The faulty science, doomism, and flawed conclusions of Deep Adaptation","key":"Qse79aVpEB"}],"key":"fX4niirQMI"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n\n\n\nThis is a backup of an article I first [published on openDemocracy](https://www.opendemocracy.net/en/oureconomy/faulty-science-doomism-and-flawed-conclusions-deep-adaptation/).\nThere is also a much shorter summary version [published in The Ecologist](https://theecologist.org/2020/jul/15/deep-adaptation-flawed-science).\nIt got considerable [traction on twitter](https://twitter.com/TEGNicholas/status/1283074865809981440).\n\nA huge number of people contributed to this piece in some form or another, not just those listed.\nI'm very grateful to all of","key":"x6P0NYosEg"}],"key":"yNwKLSgbea"},{"type":"footer","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Date: ","key":"buxieS7KRn"}],"key":"qPBb4Yf9o0"},{"type":"text","value":"July 14, 2020 | ","key":"CZN7xHhfhq"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author: ","key":"hPQrryqIsb"}],"key":"PmIJpOTeq2"},{"type":"text","value":"Tom Nicholas","key":"CBqOIdDukY"}],"key":"cqULxOK6DD"}],"urlSource":"/blog/2020/deep-pseudoscience","key":"ZeW72k8wle"},{"type":"card","url":"/blog/2020/oxford-divests","children":[{"type":"cardTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Oxford University Divestment Explained","key":"DX1eBDG5ly"}],"key":"QNHJKwSSPl"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n\nOxford University's academic congregation has passed a landmark divestment motion.\nYou can read the student newspaper [coverage here](https://www.oxfordstudent.com/2020/04/20/oxford-university-passes-motion-banning-investment-in-fossil-fuels/).\n\nI wasn't directly involved in this achievement, but I do personally know a lot of the key people who worked hard to make this happen, and I want to clarify a few things:\n\n- **It's","key":"gLX1BsDEqK"}],"key":"e3Xgrk2Soi"},{"type":"footer","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Date: ","key":"pYzVtmbWgS"}],"key":"BLQGcm3eQU"},{"type":"text","value":"April 22, 2020 | ","key":"QlnxEnM8ZP"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author: ","key":"IbCmY7UiVf"}],"key":"lPEIQuljF4"},{"type":"text","value":"Tom Nicholas","key":"ThhEq7Cd2e"}],"key":"y5FUeNT